      <title>Using movenode resets time zone of datetime fields</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/batchtool/forum/general/using_movenode_resets_time_zone_of_datetime_fields</link>
      <description>I tried moving a bunch of nodes containing datetime fields. My time zone is UTC+2. After moving them, all the fields were shifted two hours earlier. My guess is that the time zone somehow affects this, though how I am not sure. It seems counterintuitive and may be a bug in eZ publish itself.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Leif Arne Storset)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/batchtool/forum/general/using_movenode_resets_time_zone_of_datetime_fields</guid>
